quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  29,31,"And when Our Messengers (angels) came to Abraham with the glad tidings for him (of imminent birth of a son), they said, \"We are going to destroy the inhabitants of that locality (to whom Lot was sent). Indeed, the inhabitants thereof have been wicked"
  29,32,"Abraham said, \"But Lot lives therein!\" The angels said, \"We know who live therein. We shall certainly save him and his household except for his wife. She is to be among those left behind"
  29,33,"And when Our Messengers (angels) came to Lot, he was worried about them, and he felt powerless to protect them. And they said, \"Fear not, nor grieve. We shall indeed save you and your household except for your wife. She is to be among those left behind"
  29,34,"We are indeed going to bring down upon the inhabitants of this city a scourge from the heaven, for they have rebelled against Allah's commandments"
  29,35,And verily We have left thereof a manifest sign for a people who reflect
  29,36,"And to Midian (people) We sent their brother, Shu'aib. He said, \"O my people! Worship Allah, prepare yourselves for the Last Day, and do no harm on the earth wickedly"
  29,37,"And they disbelieved him! And then a violent convulsion shook them, and they lay buried in the debris of their homes"
  29,38,"And (the peoples of) AAad and Thamood! Verily, their destruction is apparent to you from their dwellings. The Satan made their deeds look good to them, and thus hindered them from the Right Path that was within their sight"